String a = &quot;hello&quot;; &lt;br&gt; 
JVM will create one string in the string pool. (FIRST STRING IN POOL)

Now, here comes the tricky part&gt; &lt;br&gt;
b = a + &quot;bye&quot;;

Internally + operator uses StringBuffer for concatenating strings. &lt;br&gt;
String b= new StringBuilder(a).append(&quot;bye&quot;).toString(); &lt;br&gt;(The toString() method of StringBuilder is returning a new String which will be definitely in the Heap since it is created with new String(...). So &quot;bye&quot; will be SECOND STRING IN POOL.)

